1. It is points accumulated for killing enemy realms members. EQ = Experience in killing mobs<br>
2. The amount of realm points you need to attain the next rank increases. (see chart). In EQ each AA point is the same Experience.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://vnboards.ign.com/message.asp?topic=31333673&amp;replies=5">vnboards.ign.com/message.asp?topic=31333673&amp;replies=5</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Realm Rank 1: --------- (+0 to all skills) <br>
Realm Rank 2: ----7,125 (+1 to all skills) <br>
Realm Rank 3: ---61,770 (+2 to all skills) <br>
Realm Rank 4: --213,750 (+3 to all skills) <br>
Realm Rank 5: --515,000 (+4 to all skills) <br>
Realm Rank 6: 1,014,000 (+5 to all skills) <br>
Realm Rank 7: 1,800,000 (+6 to all skills) <br>
<br>
3. Most skills you can get different levels for, but it will cost you. Just an example<br>
Agument Acuity<br>
Level I = 1 Realm skill points <br>
Level II = +3 realm skill points<br>
Level III = +6 Realm Skill Points<br>
Level IV = +10 Realm Skill points<br>
Level V = +14 Realm Skill points<br>
<br>
So to maximixe this realm skill, which adds +6 int, per level of skill, to your char, you need 34 realm skill points which is over 100,000 realm points.<br>
<br>
<br>
Just some of the skills you can get, using Mathais, who  has 65,000 realm points, and is Realm Rank 3 Level 0, as an example.<br>
<br>
Agument acuity level 2 skill. -- For casting players, Adds +6 points to your main power(mana) attribute Per level bought. This adds +12 int to my stats<br>
<br>
Mythic Crystal Lore skill --- another caster skill. It gives a boost of 30% of power, usable every 5 mins.<br>
<br>
I can't think of the names of others, but I have such skills that raise my magical resistances, increases the percentage of critical hits with nukes, increases my power regen. <br>
<br>
As for guild realm points, there are no added features for having these. I think in the future, if they ever guild housing comes along, these might come into play for how large of a place you can have. R <br>
<br>
